[2026-03-10T00:24:52Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011supw3q7DJJVDh4ePsPv6t","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of Container Deletion Code and Documentation\n\n### 1. Container Deletion - Code Locations\n\n#### gRPC Service Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 14, 76-80)\n- RPC method: `DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse)`\n- Request message has a single field `id` (can be run ID or container ID)\n- Response is empty (just confirms success)\n\n#### gRPC Server Implementation\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 625-658)\n- Function: `DeleteContainer(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DeleteContainerRequest)`\n- Accepts both run IDs and Docker container IDs\n- Resolves run ID to container ID by looking up in the store\n- Calls `s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID)` to delete the container\n- Clears the `ContainerKept` flag after deletion\n- Container removal is also called automatically after successful runs (lines 344-349) unless `--keep-container` flag is set or run failed\n\n#### Web API Handler\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 627-663, 130)\n- HTTP endpoint: `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` (line 130)\n- Function: `handleAPIDeleteContainer(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`\n- Gets run by ID, retrieves container manager interface\n- Calls `mgr.Remove(ctx, run.ContainerID)` to delete\n- Updates run record to clear `ContainerKept` flag\n- Returns JSON response with status\n\n#### Web UI - Delete Container Button\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 20, 24, 147, 152)\n- Delete button appears on run detail page in two conditions:\n  1. When container is \"stopped\" and run is in a terminal state (succeeded/failed/cancelled) - line 20\n  2. When container is \"available\" (kept but not running) - line 24\n- Button label: \"Delete Container\"\n- CSS class: `btn btn-danger btn-sm`\n- JavaScript function called: `deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')`\n- Real-time polling updates container status (lines 140-156)\n\n#### JavaScript Function\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 249-268)\n- Function: `window.deleteContainer(runID)`\n- Makes DELETE request to `/api/runs/{runID}/container`\n- Disables button during request\n- On success: updates container status to \"Container removed\"\n- On failure: re-enables button and shows alert with error message\n\n### 2. Container State Logic\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 342-361)\n- Function: `containerState(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) string`\n- Returns one of: `\"running\"`, `\"stopped\"`, `\"available\"`, `\"removed\"`\n- \"available\" = container exists, not running, and `ContainerKept` flag is true\n- Only \"stopped\" (with terminal run state) and \"available\" states show delete button\n\n### 3. Documentation Files in `/workspace/docs/`\n\n**Root documentation:**\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n\n**Design and Implementation Plans (in `/workspace/docs/plans/`):**\n1. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n2. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`\n3. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md`\n4. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md`\n5. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md`\n6. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init.md`\n7. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n8. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`\n9. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md`\n10. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-impl.md`\n11. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md` (Container deletion documented in Section 5, lines 227-257)\n12. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md`\n13. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`\n14. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md`\n15. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`\n16. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`\n17. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md`\n18. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md`\n19. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md`\n\n**Total:** 22 markdown files in docs directory"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a14e7dbcd5d2e3229 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 52368\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 22024</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7edfbbc1-dc50-4eeb-8153-1f29fb5433f3","uuid":"ff4593df-b8ee-4e84-a521-f47a2680c56e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all code related to deleting containers in this project. Look for:\n1. Any \"delete container\" button or UI element in web portal code\n2. Any API endpoint for deleting containers\n3. Any gRPC service definition for container deletion\n4. Search for strings like \"DeleteContainer\", \"delete_container\", \"delete-container\", \"Remove Container\" in all files\n\nAlso find all documentation files (*.md) in the docs/ directory. List them all.","agentId":"a14e7dbcd5d2e3229","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of Container Deletion Code and Documentation\n\n### 1. Container Deletion - Code Locations\n\n#### gRPC Service Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 14, 76-80)\n- RPC method: `DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse)`\n- Request message has a single field `id` (can be run ID or container ID)\n- Response is empty (just confirms success)\n\n#### gRPC Server Implementation\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 625-658)\n- Function: `DeleteContainer(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DeleteContainerRequest)`\n- Accepts both run IDs and Docker container IDs\n- Resolves run ID to container ID by looking up in the store\n- Calls `s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID)` to delete the container\n- Clears the `ContainerKept` flag after deletion\n- Container removal is also called automatically after successful runs (lines 344-349) unless `--keep-container` flag is set or run failed\n\n#### Web API Handler\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 627-663, 130)\n- HTTP endpoint: `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` (line 130)\n- Function: `handleAPIDeleteContainer(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`\n- Gets run by ID, retrieves container manager interface\n- Calls `mgr.Remove(ctx, run.ContainerID)` to delete\n- Updates run record to clear `ContainerKept` flag\n- Returns JSON response with status\n\n#### Web UI - Delete Container Button\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 20, 24, 147, 152)\n- Delete button appears on run detail page in two conditions:\n  1. When container is \"stopped\" and run is in a terminal state (succeeded/failed/cancelled) - line 20\n  2. When container is \"available\" (kept but not running) - line 24\n- Button label: \"Delete Container\"\n- CSS class: `btn btn-danger btn-sm`\n- JavaScript function called: `deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')`\n- Real-time polling updates container status (lines 140-156)\n\n#### JavaScript Function\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 249-268)\n- Function: `window.deleteContainer(runID)`\n- Makes DELETE request to `/api/runs/{runID}/container`\n- Disables button during request\n- On success: updates container status to \"Container removed\"\n- On failure: re-enables button and shows alert with error message\n\n### 2. Container State Logic\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 342-361)\n- Function: `containerState(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) string`\n- Returns one of: `\"running\"`, `\"stopped\"`, `\"available\"`, `\"removed\"`\n- \"available\" = container exists, not running, and `ContainerKept` flag is true\n- Only \"stopped\" (with terminal run state) and \"available\" states show delete button\n\n### 3. Documentation Files in `/workspace/docs/`\n\n**Root documentation:**\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n\n**Design and Implementation Plans (in `/workspace/docs/plans/`):**\n1. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n2. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`\n3. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md`\n4. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md`\n5. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md`\n6. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init.md`\n7. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n8. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`\n9. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md`\n10. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-impl.md`\n11. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md` (Container deletion documented in Section 5, lines 227-257)\n12. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md`\n13. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`\n14. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md`\n15. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`\n16. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`\n17. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md`\n18. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md`\n19. `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md`\n\n**Total:** 22 markdown files in docs directory"}],"totalDurationMs":22024,"totalTokens":52368,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":50373,"output_tokens":1388,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":602},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
